<biogHist>
<abstract>Linda Mottram is an ABC radio journalist with a career spanning over 15 years. She has experience in newspapers and television but has spent most of her working life with ABC Radio.

Linda's achievements include a Walkley Award for radio current affairs journalism for her coverage of the Kosovo conflict. She has worked as a federal parliamentary reporter, a reporter on Australian affairs for Radio Australia and a foreign correspondent in the Middle East, in Russia and in the Balkans.</abstract>
